steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"anuem","text":"Mix   agarose with   electrophoresis buffer (1X TAE) in a flask, then heat and stir until agarose is completely dissolved.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":4,"length":1},{"key":1,"offset":19,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"dt2qg","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":2,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"fht5u","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"amount","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"amount":"1","error":false,"guid":"F7B631F0FC6211EC8F6B3DDA23BFEE2C","id":0,"label":"","scientificNotation":false,"unit":6}},"1":{"type":"amount","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"amount":"100","error":false,"guid":"0C9E8540FC6311EC8F6B3DDA23BFEE2C","id":0,"label":"","scientificNotation":false,"unit":2}},"2":{"type":"notes","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"51nst","text":"Microwave can be used for heating.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4qer1","text":"Add   10000X GelRed nucleic acid stain into molten agarose and mix well.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":4,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"c29js","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"amount","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"amount":"10","error":false,"guid":"795E2E60FC6311EC8F6B3DDA23BFEE2C","id":0,"label":"","scientificNotation":false,"unit":1}}}}

Water bath can be used to control the temperature.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6932u","text":"While waiting for the cool down of molten agarose, set up and level the gel casting tray and the gel casting platform on a flat area. Inset the comb.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ajnpc","text":"Pour the molten agarose onto the tray. Immediately rinse out the flask before any remaining agarose sets in it.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9k3ql","text":"Once the gel has completely solidified, gently remove the comb by pulling it up slowly and vertically.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"82mvp","text":"Carefully place the tray in the gel tank. Add electrophoresis buffer (1X TAE) until covering the whole gel surface.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"i5fc","text":"While waiting for gel solidification, prepare the samples as follows:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"49t5d","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"rmf4","text":"Mixing the components:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4tonm","text":"6X gel loading dye                     X μL","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9lb3h","text":"DNA sample/DNA ladder       5X μL","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"a48sh","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"99jsg","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"25lna","text":"In order to receive a clearer ladder photograph, the recipe for DNA ladder with gel loading dye is recommended as follows:","type":"unstyled"},{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"e9oke","text":"","type":"unstyled"},{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"cqf48","text":"6X gel loading dye                     X μL","type":"unstyled"},{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"ta3v","text":"DNA ladder                                 X μL","type":"unstyled"},{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"9suu9","text":"Double distilled water             4X μL","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"aurst","text":"Pipette the prepared samples using a P20 (2μL-20μL) pipette to the wells.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2g4o","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"dc24r","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6ml4","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"afv5o","text":"The samples should sink to the bottom of the wells and displace the buffer.","type":"unstyled"},{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"vs6o","text":"The amount for each load should be decided by multiple facters like DNA concentration and gel concentration. The DNA amount we use normally is from 10ng to 100ng, or 5μL to 10μL in volume.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"dk4l","text":"Run the gels at 90 V, approximately 50 mA, for 90 min.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
